#. type: Title #
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:1
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:4
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Proof of Work"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:7
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "> Proof of work is a way to legitimize untrusted party\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "What exactly is proof of work?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:11
#, markdown-text
msgid "Proof of work is a cryptographic proof that untrusted party committed significant computational resources to solve artificial problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:13
#, markdown-text
msgid "Technically, the \"proof\" is simply a solution to the problem at hand."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "It's all about legitimizing untrusted party"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:17
#, markdown-text
msgid "How an untrusted party on the Internet could earn any level of your trust?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:19
#, markdown-text
msgid "It can prove its commitment by solving agreed computationally hard problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:21
#, markdown-text
msgid "For example, by requiring untrusted party to perform a hard computation before you accept their connection, you limit connections only to \"committed\" parties."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:23
#, markdown-text
msgid "In another example, you could require PoW to be attached to incoming e-mails to make spam prohibitively expensive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:24
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Work must be otherwise useless"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:27
#, markdown-text
msgid "The work on and solution to \"computationally hard problem\" cannot be useful in any other way than to prove the commitment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:29
#, markdown-text
msgid "If the work is useful elsewhere then it doesn't prove commitment to you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:31
#, markdown-text
msgid "The problem must be artificial. Otherwise incentives are skewed and the whole scheme breaks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:32
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Strong asymmetry"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:35
#, markdown-text
msgid "The requirement for proof of work scheme is strong asymmetry for work vs verification resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:36
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The work must be arbitrarily hard. At the same time proof verification must remain dirt cheap (in terms of computational resources).  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:39
#, markdown-text
msgid "Cheap verification is critical because at this stage we are dealing with potentially huge number of untrusted parties, who could DoS the verifier by submitting invalid proofs. Such proofs should be trivial to discard."
msgstr ""
